<TITLE> Fire at power plant shuts 210 MW unit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Norshingdi, Apr 5 (bdnews24.com)A fire has forced the closure of a 210 megawatts unit in the country's largest Thermal power plant in Ghorashal on Monday. The plant security guard Solayman, 30, was severely injured in the fire and was sent to Dhaka Medical College and Hospital. The Ghorashal plant has an installed capacity of 950MW, but because of its age can only generate 845MW. Chief engineer of the plant Tomal Chakrabarti said the fire was ignited when a cable of one of the units was disconnected. Firefighters from Polash rushed to the scene and put out the fire after 30 minutes. A 320KV transmission substation was also partially damaged  though the engineer could not estimate how badly. A Power Development Board spokesperson told bdnews24.com that the unit could be operational by Monday night. In addition to the fire, two units of the plant with a combined capacity of 265 MW are currently closed due to forced maintenance. Until the damaged unit is fixed, the plant will only be producing 380MW  out of a possible 845MW capacity - the PDP official said bdne
